PHASE 5: IMPLEMENTATION PLAN (12-18 Month Roadmap)
=====================================================

=== TRANCHE 1: Foundation (Months 1-2) — DO NOW ===

Step 1: Fix Positional Encoding
  - File: src/models/transformer.py
  - Change: Learned `self.pos` → Sinusoidal PositionalEncoding
  - Benefit: Better extrapolation beyond training sequence length
  - Code reference: Research doc → PositionalEncoding class

Step 2: Create Production Inference Engine
  - File: src/engine/inference.py (NEW)
  - Components:
    a) ColossusInferenceEngine class (5-second inference cycle)
    b) Real-time signal generation with SOC tracking
    c) Simulation mode (like research doc)
  - Files: Depends on signal.py, transformer.py

Step 3: Automated Drive Checkpointing
  - File: src/engine/trainer.py (update)
  - Change: Auto-save every N steps + save to PROJECT_DIR/checkpoints/
  - Benefit: Colab crash recovery

=== TRANCHE 2: Integration (Months 3-6) ===

Step 4: Live Sensor API Layer
  - File: src/data/sensors.py (NEW)
  - APIs:
    a) GPU telemetry → NVIDIA DCGM simulator → real DCGM
    b) Weather → NOAA REST API → hourly forecasts
    c) Grid → CAISO/PJM API → frequency + import limits
    d) Megapack → Tesla SCADA → SOC + charge/discharge status

Step 5: Model Interpretability
  - File: src/engine/explain.py (NEW)
  - Methods:
    a) Attention rollout visualization (heatmap over time)
    b) Feature importance (GRN gate values)
    c) SHAP values for each prediction
  - Output: JSON explanation for grid operator dashboard

=== TRANCHE 3: Scale (Months 7-12) ===

Step 6: Multi-Cluster Global Training
  - File: src/data/generator.py (update)
  - Generate data for N clusters with correlated but independent GP workloads
  - Train single model on all clusters → better generalization

Step 7: Adaptive Loss Thresholding
  - File: src/models/losses.py (update)
  - Dynamic spike threshold based on real-time grid conditions
  - Integration with grid API for import limit awareness

=== TRANCHE 4: Edge (Months 13-18) ===

Step 8: Real Weather Nowcasting
  - Edge cameras + satellite imagery + local vision model
  - 60-second cloud movement prediction
  - Integration with solar panel output prediction

Step 9: Supercapacitor Coordination Layer
  - Hardware integration with supercapacitor bank
  - Microsecond response layer on top of prediction layer

=== CRITICAL PATH ===
  The critical dependency chain is:
  Fix positional encoding → Inference engine → Live sensors → Scale
  Everything else can run in parallel.
